- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with combinatorial aspects of sparse graphs, such as counting the number of subsets of a given set, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper provides explicit bounds on the number of types in sparse graphs, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with algorithmic aspects of sparse graphs, such as computing the number of subsets of a given set, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category.
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper deals with graph classes and their properties, which is a topic of interest in this sub-category.
